The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Heat claims cop on duty
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Heat claims cop on duty
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                            Tiger Mobile: Heat threat                                  
	Jamshedpur, April 25: Ravindra Pandey, a constable of district polices Tiger Mobile force, died of sunstroke this afternoon.        
	According to sources at Golmuri Police Lines, the 35-year-old policeman was posted on special duty near G Town Club since 10am. Around 2pm, he returned to his Baroda Ghaat colony home in Bagbera after feeling uncomfortable and dizzy. But as his condition deteriorated, Pandeys family members rushed him to Rajasthan Seva Sadan in Jugsalai, where he collapsed.         
	Immediately, he was shifted to MGM Medical College Hospital where he was declared brought dead.        
	Arun Kumar, the doctor who was on emergency duty at the medical college in the afternoon, said: The patient had already died before being brought to the hospital. I cannot say anything about the symptoms that led to his death.        
	Soon after the news of his death spread, superintendent of police Naveen Kumar Singh and deputy superintendents of police visited the medical college. Office-bearers of the Police Mens Association expressed concern over his sudden death.        
	A post-mortem was conducted in the evening and the cause of his death was ascertained as sunstroke.        
	Singh said policemen would be given an orientation training on how to evade sunstroke. Certain steps would be made compulsory for them to ward off heat, Singh said.        
	The city recorded the highest temperature at 42.3C, 2 degrees above normal, with no rain being predicted in the next 72 hours.                                                                                                                                           
